quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  4,97,"Verily, the angels when they take the souls of those who had wronged themselves, they say, \"What state were you in?\" They say, \"We were but weak (and oppressed) in the earth;\" They say, \"Was not Allah´s earth wide enough for"
  4,98,"Save for the weak (oppressed) men, and women, and children, who had no means, stratagem or guidance"
  4,99,"These it may be Allah will pardon, for Allah is Clement and Forgiving"
  4,100,"Whoever flees (migrates) in the way of Allah shall find in the earth many a spacious refuge; and he who goes forth from his house, fleeing unto Allah and His prophet, and then death catches him up - his reward becomes incumbent on Allah, and Allah is Forg"